  "prompt": "What is Alma Mater society?",
  "response": "The Alma Mater Society (AMS) is typically a student society or organization found at universities, most notably at Queen's University in Kingston, Ontario, Canada. The term \"Alma Mater\" is Latin for \"nourishing mother,\" symbolizing the university as a nurturing institution for its students.\n\nAt Queen's University, the AMS represents undergraduate students and offers various services, advocacy, and events to enhance student life. These services can include health and dental plans, academic advocacy, clubs and societies, and social events. The AMS is governed by a council composed of elected student representatives who work to address the needs and concerns of the student body.\n\nOther universities may have similar organizations with different names, but the purpose remains the same: to support and represent the student community. If you are referring to a specific Alma Mater Society at a different institution, the details might vary, but the general concept would be similar.",
